<subSubSection pageId="254" pageNumber="859" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="254.[1378,2585,1434,2291]" pageId="254" pageNumber="859">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1380,1728,2064,2093]" pageId="254" pageNumber="859">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Sumatran Mountain Spiny Rat has a relatively small distribution but faces 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hatt" authorityYear="1934" box="[2350,2479,2103,2132]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Thamnomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="254" pageNumber="733" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">no major</taxonomicName>
known threats. It occurs in Kerinci Seblat National Park. Additional research is needed to fully understand its natural history, taxonomy, and threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
